<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "data_processing_parser",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "data/input.json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now I need to validate the parsed data. Since the validator requires a schema, I'll use a default schema that allows any valid JSON structure. This is a reasonable default for testing purposes. I'll pass the parsed data from the previous step.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "data_processing_validator",
  "parameters": {
    "schema": {"type": "object", "additionalProperties": true},
    "data": {}
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll transform the data. Since the input data is in JSON format and I want to keep it structured, I'll transform it to JSON as well. This is a reasonable default for testing purposes.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "data_processing_transformer",
  "parameters": {
    "input_format": "json",
    "output_format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

I'll use the integration_mapper tool to transform the data from JSON to JSON format. This is a reasonable default for testing purposes.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "integration_mapper",
  "parameters": {
    "input_format": "json",
    "output_format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>
